Retrieves data for specified data elements from KHIS analytics tables

Source: R/get_analytics.R
get_analytics.Rd

get_analytics fetches raw data from the KHIS analytics data tables for a given period and data element(s), without performing any aggregation.

get_analytics(
  element_ids,
  start_date,
  end_date = NULL,
  level = c("kenya", "county", "subcounty", "ward", "facility"),
  organisations = NULL,
  categories = NULL,
  elements = NULL,
  khis_session = dynGet("khis_default_session", inherits = TRUE),
  retry = 1,
  verbosity = 0
)

Arguments

element_ids

A vector of data element IDs for which to retrieve data. Required.

start_date

The starting date for data retrieval in the format 'YYYY-MM-dd'. Required.

end_date

The ending date for data retrieval (default is the current date).

level

The desired data granularity: "kenya", "county", "subcounty", "ward", or "facility".

organisations

A list of organization units to filter the data. If NULL, downloaded using get_organisation_units().

categories

A list of categories to include. If NULL, downloaded using get_categories().

elements

A list of data elements to include. If NULL, downloaded using get_data_elements().

khis_session

A KHIS session object to use for the API call. Defaults to the default session.

retry

The number of times to retry the API call if it fails. Defaults to 1.

verbosity

The level of detail to log for the API call. Defaults to 0 (no logging).

Value

A tibble containing the retrieved data.

Details

  • Retrieves data directly from KHIS analytics tables.

  • Returns a tibble (data frame) with detailed information, including:

    • Geographical identifiers (kenya, county, subcounty, ward, facility, depending on level)

    • Reporting period (month, year, fiscal year)

    • Data element names

    • Category options

    • Reported values

  • Supports optional arguments for providing organization lists, data elements, and categories.

  • Allows specifying KHIS session objects, retry attempts, and logging verbosity.

See also

get_organisation_units(), get_data_elements(), get_categories()
